&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Occupational Therapist - Rotational / Static Posts Available &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Occupational Therapy Team at Liverpool University Hospital’s NHS Foundation Trusts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based across Aintree, The Royal Liverpool and Broadgreen sites in the City of Liverpool, employees at Liverpool University Hospitals are ideally located to benefit from the vibrant and fast paced social aspects of the city with its famous warm welcomes and unique attractions, exciting events, world class sport and excellent, broad musical heritage. The Trust has accommodation to offer and all sites are located only a short distance from the city centre with excellent transport links.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trust hosts the Major Trauma Centre for Cheshire, Merseyside and the Isle of Man and offers rotations in Major Trauma, Trauma Orthopaedics, Elective Orthopaedics, First Response, A&amp;E, Frailty, Critical care, Medicine / Surgery, Stroke, Elderly Acute, Gerontology, Acute Neuro, Acute Intervention, Rehab, Early Supported Discharge (ESD) team and Aintree at Home. The available rotations will allow you to consolidate your knowledge and skills across a broad range of clinical areas and locations in a forward thinking, supportive and dynamic environment, alongside other skilled Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapist, Dietitians, Speech and Language Therapists, Assistant Practitioners and Generic Therapy Assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Occupational Therapists work as part of the wider Integrated Multi-Therapies Service which provides the opportunity to be involved in service development and leadership within a wider therapy team. As a teaching hospital there is a strong commitment to continuing professional development supported by the Trust’s appraisal system. You will bring the drive to develop yourself, your colleagues and your service in this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be a requirement to work across a 7 day service within the rotations and across various sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlexandra SpearittJob titleDeputy CBM therapiesEmail addressalexandra.spearitt@liverpoolft.nhs.ukTelephone number0151 529 3340Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits contact: Alex Spearritt, Deputy clinical business manager &amp; workforce lead –Therapies via email: Alexandra.spearritt@liverpoolft.nhs.uk or on 07971 495047 or Helen Ashcroft-Kelso, Clinical Lead Therapist via email: Helen.ashcroft-kelso@liverpoolft.nhs.uk or on 0151 529 8084&lt;/p&gt;
